title: For Sale:  Romanian Dragunov sniper rifle
postcontent:
This is a used, factory built Romanian Dragunov sniper rifle, complete with original military scope(not the imported version) and all of the accessories pictured. 
These rifles, also known as a Romak-3, SSG-97, and PSL, are extremely accurate and reliable. The Dragunov design has been in use since the mid 60's, and is still the 
official design of Russia and other Com-bloc countries. This is the Romanian version, which improved on the Russian design as far as reliability goes. This is a great weapon for several reasons. First, it uses the same type of action that an AK-47 uses, which makes it drag-through-the-mud reliable. Second, it's semi-automatic, which means if you miss with the first shot, you have an immediate chance to make up for it. Third, it uses a very powerful 7.62x54R caliber bullet, which is a monster round. The large size of the round and the long barrel of the rifle combine to allow shooting out to 1000yds. These features make the perfect long-range weapon for any situation. This rifle comes complete with scope (very cool, built in range-finder reticle which was originally lit with radioactive Tritium), cleaning kit, broken-shell extractor, small spare parts, cleaning rod, oil bottle, leather sling, owner's manual provided by importer, and a hardcase.

title: For Sale:   Russian SVD Dragunov 4x24 scope and Russian 1PN58 Night Vision scope
postcontent: A used, excellent condition soviet Dragunov scope. These would have been the type of scopes imported with the Tiger rifles and this one has a serial number marked on the inside of the scope mount. These are generally regarded as being of higher quality than the commercially available scopes. The illuminated reticle has not been tested and a Russian 1PN58 night vision scope. These were designed for Soviet weapons with a side rail and have been used extensively on the Dragunov family of rifles. The 1PN58 was the new and improved version of the 1PN34. In my opinion it is greatly improved. These optics are considered Gen 2 and they were space age at the time they came out. These optics are still very effective. This scope is in very good to excellent condition externally. It comes with the original carrying case and two original batteries as well as the AK74 ballistic cam (PK cams are out there for the SVD).

The SIG SAUER® P226®, writes the factory, is the pistol that set the standard by which all other combat handguns are measured. The exceptional ergonomics and balance make this fullsize pistol easy to handle. Its longer barrel yields better ballistic performance and accuracy. The P226 MK25 is identical to the pistol carried by the U.S. Navy SEALs-the fleet’s special warfare operators. The railed P226 chambered in 9mm and engraved with an anchor on the left side of the slide is the official sidearm of the SEALs. Photo specimen is one of only a few released to the NRA Foundation and sold exclusively through Friends of NRA fundraisers in 2013 only. It comes in a special Pelican hard case with fired brass case, instruction manual, factory papers and lock. Box bears the Friends of NRA Logo. Medallion included commemorates the Navy SEALs Foundation, and Sig has donated to that foundation with each pistol produced. This edition has UID labels on components. Manufacturer is Sig Sauer Inc. of Exeter, NH. Construction is steel barrel, slide, and parts in Nitron® finish, with Black hard anodized finish alloy frame. Specs on the 226 are what S&W calls traditional double action, 10 pound vicinity double action trigger pull from the decocked position on the first shot, then single action 4 pound vicinity on subsequent shots during the firing session. The Sig 226, of course, does not have a manually operated safety. It has a decocker lever to put the car in park. Sig has a firing pin block safety that prevents accidental discharge if the pistol is dropped, yet even with that, Sigs have the best single action trigger pull of all from the factory. Weight empty is 34 ounces; finish is black; barrel is 4.40 inch chrome lined; and it has the conventional white bar rear and white dot front sights. Accessory or light rail is incorporated with the frame. Sights are MH3 Siglite luminous Night Sights, made for Sig by Mepro. These are always point of aim from the factory. Overall length is 7.7 inches from the muzzle to the grip frame strut, height 5.5 inches, overall width 1.5 inches; sight radius 6.3 inches. This 226 MK25 comes with a total of three each fifteen round magazines, steel floorplate with matte anti-friction steel bodies, made for Sig by Mec-Gar in Italy. This specimen was never out of NRA custody until we got it. It has never been fired or loaded.
